div.p:
"Oh no—I have so much to amuse me. I have my birds to feed, my flowers to water;
                  if I would play and sing I have my harp and music; if I would work there is my
                  'broidery—oh no, it is home to me and I'm happy!"

"Oh, such a lovely garden, even at this season teeming with fruits and flowers;
                  fountains sending showers of silver high up in the air, and those beautiful women
                  walking about—who are they?"

